Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.30,0:22:25.23,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,好，我去追蹤麥克斯和亨裏克\N{\reng_1 - 1080}Okay, I'll track down Max and Henrik,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.23,0:22:27.90,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,但我們得知道他們的僱主是誰\N{\reng_1 - 1080}but we need to know who they're working for.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.90,0:22:29.47,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,很可能和當初僱傭托馬斯的\N{\reng_1 - 1080}It was probably the same client{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.47,0:22:31.20,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,<i>是同一個客戶</i>\N{\reng_1 - 1080}who hired Tomas in the first place.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.21,0:22:33.57,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,其他人都不知道搶劫的事\N{\reng_1 - 1080}Nobody else knew about the robbery.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.58,0:22:35.41,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,再說了，給那兩人錢去殺了托馬斯\N{\reng_1 - 1080}Plus, paying those two to kill Tomas{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.41,0:22:38.58,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,要比一起支付三個人便宜多了\N{\reng_1 - 1080}is cheaper than paying all three.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.58,0:22:40.58,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,本來就是\N{\reng_1 - 1080}Well, it is.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.58,0:22:43.88,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,那麼…\N{\reng_1 - 1080}So...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.88,0:22:46.89,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,你的客戶是誰？\N{\reng_1 - 1080}who's your client?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.89,0:22:49.45,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,你的客戶又是誰？\N{\reng_1 - 1080}Who's yours?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.46,0:22:51.26,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,你不只是個小偷\N{\reng_1 - 1080}You're not just a thief,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.26,0:22:52.83,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,而且絕不可能是單干的\N{\reng_1 - 1080}and you're definitely not working alone.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.83,0:22:57.10,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,所以我為什麼要相信你？\N{\reng_1 - 1080}So why should I even trust you?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.10,0:22:59.40,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,你還想跟我談信任問題啊？\N{\reng_1 - 1080}You wanna talk about trust, huh?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.40,0:23:02.47,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,你剛為某些危險份子\N{\reng_1 - 1080}Uh, you just stole a very dangerous virus{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.47,0:23:03.67,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,偷了極度致命的病毒\N{\reng_1 - 1080}for some very dangerous people.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.67,0:23:04.97,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,聽著，當初要是知道那是病毒\N{\reng_1 - 1080}Look, I never would have done that{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.97,0:23:06.14,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,我根本不會沾手\N{\reng_1 - 1080}if I knew what I was taking.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.14,0:23:07.30,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,我雖然不是聖人\N{\reng_1 - 1080}I'm not a saint,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.31,0:23:09.84,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,可某些事情，確實超出底線了\N{\reng_1 - 1080}but some things are too far,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.84,0:23:12.14,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,哪怕對於我這樣的人\N{\reng_1 - 1080}even for a man like me.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.15,0:23:16.81,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,是哦，估計你客戶的道德準則就遠不如你了\N{\reng_1 - 1080}Well, I doubt your client has the same high moral standards.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.82,0:23:18.08,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,告訴我名字\N{\reng_1 - 1080}I need a name.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.08,0:23:19.08,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,壓根沒有\N{\reng_1 - 1080}Never got one.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.08,0:23:20.52,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,都是匿名郵件\N{\reng_1 - 1080}Anonymous emails,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.52,0:23:22.45,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,一次性電匯付款\N{\reng_1 - 1080}payments by one-time wire transfer.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.46,0:23:26.52,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,不用名字，對大家都好\N{\reng_1 - 1080}It's better for everyone if we don't use names.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.53,0:23:29.76,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,但我一定要揪出那個幕後黑手\N{\reng_1 - 1080}But I'm gonna find the bastard behind this.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.76,0:23:32.46,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,我會偷回那些病毒\N{\reng_1 - 1080}I'm gonna steal those vials back,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.46,0:23:35.20,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,要那傢伙付出代價\N{\reng_1 - 1080}and I'm gonna make him pay.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.20,0:23:38.33,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,一起幹不？\N{\reng_1 - 1080}You in?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.34,0:23:39.64,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,你覺得呢？\N{\reng_1 - 1080}What do you think?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.31,0:23:44.77,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,我有個朋友\N{\reng_1 - 1080}I have a friend{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.78,0:23:47.68,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,他可以讓那些匿名郵件\N{\reng_1 - 1080}who can make those anonymous emails{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.68,0:23:49.48,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,露出些端倪\N{\reng_1 - 1080}way less anonymous.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.05,0:23:56.99,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,這裏就是奇跡發生的地方\N{\reng_1 - 1080}So this is where the magic happens.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.99,0:24:00.16,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,租下900多平米的辦公室\N{\reng_1 - 1080}Rented 10,000 square feet of office space and filled it{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.16,0:24:02.62,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,擺滿了最新型3D打印機\N{\reng_1 - 1080}with state-of-the-art 3-D printers.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.63,0:24:05.06,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,一千二百萬幾乎都花在這上面了\N{\reng_1 - 1080}Almost all the 12 million went to paying for these,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.06,0:24:07.23,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,不過一旦它們上線運行\N{\reng_1 - 1080}but once they're up and running,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.23,0:24:10.33,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,我們將在這裏生產所有的平板電腦\N{\reng_1 - 1080}we'll be making all the tablets right here{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.33,0:24:11.83,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,就在紐約\N{\reng_1 - 1080}in New York.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.84,0:24:14.64,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,這台是樣機\N{\reng_1 - 1080}That's our prototype.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.64,0:24:17.97,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,想像一下，全州每個孩子人手一台平板\N{\reng_1 - 1080}Just imagine giving one of those to every kid in the state.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.97,0:24:19.07,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,不可思議啊\N{\reng_1 - 1080}Amazing.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.08,0:24:20.54,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,<i>我會告之州長</i>\N{\reng_1 - 1080}I'll tell the Governor{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.54,0:24:23.55,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,撥款得到妥善使用\N{\reng_1 - 1080}our grant money is in good hands.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.55,0:24:27.68,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,你們為什麼要安裝攝像頭？\N{\reng_1 - 1080}Why are you guys putting up cameras?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.69,0:24:31.02,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,我是公關辦公室的，傑羅德\N{\reng_1 - 1080}I'm from the Public Relations Office, Jerrod.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.02,0:24:32.69,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,<i>州長想把製作平板的過程</i>\N{\reng_1 - 1080}The Governor wants a time lapse{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.69,0:24:34.66,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,<i>拍成縮時攝影放在我們的網站上</i>\N{\reng_1 - 1080}of your tablets being made to put on our website.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.66,0:24:37.56,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,或者說一部邪惡的人工智能\N{\reng_1 - 1080}Or an evil AI wants to keep a close eye{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.56,0:24:39.19,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,想密切監視它的小小洗腦工具\N{\reng_1 - 1080}on its baby brainwashers.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.20,0:24:40.76,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,肯定是我們入侵威爾金斯的電腦\N{\reng_1 - 1080}Our intrusion into Wilkins' computer{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.76,0:24:42.53,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,引起了撒瑪利亞的警覺\N{\reng_1 - 1080}must have put Samaritan on alert,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.53,0:24:44.60,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,讓我們要做的事\N{\reng_1 - 1080}making it that much more difficult{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.60,0:24:47.17,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,更加困難了\N{\reng_1 - 1080}to do what we must.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.17,0:24:49.27,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,<i>是困難，不過…</i>\N{\reng_1 - 1080}Difficult but...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.27,0:24:51.34,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,我們會找到辦法的\N{\reng_1 - 1080}we'll find a way in.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.91,0:24:59.91,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,不過首先我們得去買點東西\N{\reng_1 - 1080}But first we'll need to go shopping.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.62,0:25:05.52,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,<i>找到病毒了嗎，裏斯先生？</i>\N{\reng_1 - 1080}Any progress finding the virus, Mr. Reese?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.52,0:25:07.72,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,我找到了麥克斯和亨裏克\N{\reng_1 - 1080}Well, I tracked down Max and Henrik,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.72,0:25:09.42,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,不過我覺得他們沒法開口了\N{\reng_1 - 1080}but I don't think they're gonna talk.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.42,0:25:11.59,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,我搜了他們的屍體\N{\reng_1 - 1080}I searched their bodies.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.59,0:25:13.43,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,<i>沒有手機，沒有錢包</i>\N{\reng_1 - 1080}No phones, no wallets,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.43,0:25:15.46,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,也沒看到病毒\N{\reng_1 - 1080}and no sign of the virus.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.46,0:25:17.30,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,所以看來托馬斯不是唯一一個\N{\reng_1 - 1080}So it would seem that Tomas is not the only one{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.30,0:25:19.37,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,被這位客戶騙了的人\N{\reng_1 - 1080}that this client has double-crossed.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.37,0:25:22.10,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,如果這兩個傢伙知道他是誰\N{\reng_1 - 1080}Well, if these guys knew who he was,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.10,0:25:24.77,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,也許其他人也會知道\N{\reng_1 - 1080}maybe someone else does too.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.54,0:25:31.88,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,<i>你在浪費我的時間</i>\N{\reng_1 - 1080}You waste my time.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.88,0:25:35.45,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,那項毒品指控是虛假的\N{\reng_1 - 1080}Your drug charge is podrobka.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.45,0:25:37.12,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,你立不了案\N{\reng_1 - 1080}You'll never make it stick.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.12,0:25:38.62,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,沒必要立案\N{\reng_1 - 1080}I won't have to.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.62,0:25:41.29,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,我現在是在調查兇殺案\N{\reng_1 - 1080}See, it's a homicide investigation now.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.06,0:25:44.26,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,你不想告訴我\N{\reng_1 - 1080}You wouldn't want to tell me{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.26,0:25:46.89,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,你朋友托馬斯的事嗎？\N{\reng_1 - 1080}about your friend Tomas, would you?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.90,0:25:49.30,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,我從昨天起就在這兒了\N{\reng_1 - 1080}I've been here since yesterday.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.30,0:25:51.06,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,他的死跟我沒關係\N{\reng_1 - 1080}I have nothing to do with his death.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.07,0:25:52.96,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,我沒說過死的人是他\N{\reng_1 - 1080}I never said he was the one who died.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.97,0:25:57.24,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,我在調查的這起兇殺案，死了兩個人\N{\reng_1 - 1080}The homicide I'm working, it's a double.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.24,0:26:00.31,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,看見沒，不管是誰雇你們三個幹掉托馬斯\N{\reng_1 - 1080}See, whoever hired you three to take out Tomas,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.31,0:26:02.44,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,這就是他們的結算方式\N{\reng_1 - 1080}this is how they settled the check.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.44,0:26:04.28,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,現在我要是你\N{\reng_1 - 1080}Now, if I were you,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.28,0:26:06.48,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,就坐上隨便去哪兒的第一班飛機\N{\reng_1 - 1080}I'd like to be sipping a nice glass of champagne{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.48,0:26:08.31,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,啜一杯上好的香檳了\N{\reng_1 - 1080}on our first flight to nowhere,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.32,0:26:10.75,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,而不是坐以待斃等著坐牢\N{\reng_1 - 1080}instead of a sitting duck in a jail cell.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.75,0:26:15.85,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,不過也許我是在浪費你時間吧\N{\reng_1 - 1080}But maybe I'm wasting your time.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.62,0:26:20.29,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,我喜歡托馬斯\N{\reng_1 - 1080}I like Tomas.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.29,0:26:22.33,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,不過還是得公事公辦\N{\reng_1 - 1080}But business is business.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.33,0:26:24.53,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,怎麼談的交易？\N{\reng_1 - 1080}What was the deal?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.93,0:26:28.63,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,每人再多五十萬\N{\reng_1 - 1080}Half a million extra each{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.64,0:26:32.14,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,給我，麥克斯和亨裏克\N{\reng_1 - 1080}for me, Max, and Henrik.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.14,0:26:34.81,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,托馬斯撬開保險箱，然後…\N{\reng_1 - 1080}Tomas cracks the vault and...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.94,0:26:38.81,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,反正計劃是那樣的\N{\reng_1 - 1080}Well, that was the plan anyway.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.81,0:26:41.21,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,計劃？誰的計劃？客戶是誰？\N{\reng_1 - 1080}Plan? Whose plan? Who was the client?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.21,0:26:43.28,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,就跟其他活兒一樣\N{\reng_1 - 1080}It was like the rest of the job.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.28,0:26:46.22,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,一次性匯款，匿名郵件\N{\reng_1 - 1080}One-time wires, no-name emails.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.22,0:26:48.99,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,但不管這個人是誰\N{\reng_1 - 1080}But whoever he was,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.99,0:26:50.39,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,他無所不知\N{\reng_1 - 1080}he knew everything.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.39,0:26:52.06,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,他知道托馬斯是唯一一個\N{\reng_1 - 1080}He knew Tomas was the only person{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.06,0:26:54.12,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,能成功實現這種計劃的人\N{\reng_1 - 1080}to pull off a plan like this.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.13,0:26:58.16,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,他也知道如果知道偷的是什麼\N{\reng_1 - 1080}He also knew Tomas wouldn't have done it{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.16,0:27:01.00,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,托馬斯是不會幹的\N{\reng_1 - 1080}if he knew what he was stealing.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.57,0:27:05.40,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,他還知道要你們三個人出賣朋友\N{\reng_1 - 1080}And he knew for the right price{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.40,0:27:08.20,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,什麼價碼合適\N{\reng_1 - 1080}you three would turn on a friend.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.58,0:27:19.65,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,好了，哈羅德，我們來這兒幹嘛？\N{\reng_1 - 1080}Okay, Harold, why are we here?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.65,0:27:21.25,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,這是線索，肖女士\N{\reng_1 - 1080}It's bread crumbs, Ms. Shaw.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.25,0:27:25.19,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,我試圖跟蹤托馬斯和卡佳提供的\N{\reng_1 - 1080}My attempts to trace the emails and wire transfers{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.19,0:27:27.02,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,郵件和匯款記錄\N{\reng_1 - 1080}provided by Tomas and Katya{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.02,0:27:29.56,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,<i>但還是沒查到他們客戶的身份</i>\N{\reng_1 - 1080}have yet to reveal their client's identity.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.56,0:27:31.26,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,不過昨天這位客戶轉了筆賬\N{\reng_1 - 1080}But yesterday the client wired money{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.26,0:27:33.86,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,來支付位於這個地址的存儲費用\N{\reng_1 - 1080}to pay for storage at that address.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.86,0:27:35.83,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,Knight＆Morris公司\N{\reng_1 - 1080}Knight & Morris,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.83,0:27:39.27,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,紐約最古老、最安全的存儲設施\N{\reng_1 - 1080}the oldest and most secure storage facility in New York,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.27,0:27:41.87,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,存放的物品包括無價的傳家寶\N{\reng_1 - 1080}housing everything from priceless heirlooms{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.87,0:27:43.24,chs_2 - 1080,,0,0,0,,到文藝復興時期藝術品\N{\reng_1 - 1080}to renaissance art.{\r}
